# Modern CSS Techniques for Responsive Design

CSS has evolved significantly in recent years, providing powerful tools for creating responsive layouts. Let's explore some of the most important modern CSS techniques.

## CSS Grid

CSS Grid is a two-dimensional layout system that revolutionizes how we design web pages:

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
  gap: 20px;
}
```

## Flexbox

Flexbox provides a one-dimensional layout model that's perfect for distributing space:

```css
.nav {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}
```

## Custom Properties (CSS Variables)

CSS variables allow you to define reusable values:

```css
:root {
  --primary-color: #4CAF50;
  --spacing-unit: 8px;
}

.button {
  background-color: var(--primary-color);
  padding: calc(var(--spacing-unit) * 2);
}
```

## Container Queries

Container queries allow components to adapt based on their container size:

```css
.card {
  container-type: inline-size;
}

@container (min-width: 400px) {
  .card-content {
    display: flex;
  }
}
```

## Responsive Typography

Use clamp() for fluid typography that scales between minimum and maximum sizes:

```css
h1 {
  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
}
```

## Conclusion

Modern CSS provides powerful tools for creating responsive, maintainable layouts. By mastering these techniques, you can build websites that look great on any device.
